It's the only way...

762
00:58:16,643 --> 00:58:18,686
...they'd let me stay.

763
00:58:18,978 --> 00:58:21,357
This is crazy.
You don't want to do this.

764
00:58:21,564 --> 00:58:23,650
Put it, put it down.

765
00:58:32,408 --> 00:58:33,910
Take it easy.

766
00:58:34,577 --> 00:58:36,162
You'll be all right.

767
00:58:37,205 --> 00:58:38,790
Him? What about me?

768
00:58:38,998 --> 00:58:41,418
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!

769
00:58:41,584 --> 00:58:43,503
You've had worse from shaving.

770
00:58:43,711 --> 00:58:45,797
What did you do to set him off?

771
00:58:46,005 --> 00:58:48,258
Nothing.
I come in here to say farewell.

772
00:58:48,842 --> 00:58:51,511
Ain't you heard?
His parole's come through.

773
00:58:53,847 --> 00:58:56,641
I just don't understand
what happened in there.

774
00:58:56,850 --> 00:58:59,644
Old man's crazy as a rat
in a tin shithouse.

775
00:58:59,853 --> 00:59:01,771
That's enough out of you.

776
00:59:01,937 --> 00:59:04,690
- Heard he had you shitting your pants.
- Fuck you.

777
00:59:04,941 --> 00:59:06,151
Knock it off.

778
00:59:07,110 --> 00:59:08,570
Brooks ain't no bug.

779
00:59:12,407 --> 00:59:14,159
He's just institutionalized.

780
00:59:15,535 --> 00:59:17,454
"Institutionalized," my ass.

781
00:59:17,662 --> 00:59:21,666
The man's been in here 50 years,
Heywood, 50 years!

782
00:59:21,874 --> 00:59:23,626
This is all he knows.

783
00:59:23,793 --> 00:59:26,129
In here, he's an important man...

784
00:59:26,296 --> 00:59:27,422
...an educated man.

785
00:59:28,213 --> 00:59:30,133
Outside, he's nothing.

786
00:59:31,009 --> 00:59:34,512
Just a used-up con
with arthritis in both hands.

787
00:59:34,720 --> 00:59:37,724
Probably couldn't get a library card
if he tried.

788
00:59:37,974 --> 00:59:39,726
You know what I'm trying to say?

789
00:59:39,976 --> 00:59:42,896
I do believe
you're talking out of your ass.

790
00:59:44,147 --> 00:59:46,399
You believe whatever you want.

791
00:59:46,983 --> 00:59:49,402
But I tell you these walls are funny.

792
00:59:50,987 --> 00:59:52,654
First you hate them.

793
00:59:54,491 --> 00:59:56,408
Then you get used to them.

794
00:59:58,328 --> 01:00:00,330
Enough time passes...

795
01:00:00,996 --> 01:00:02,999
...you get so you depend on them.

796
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:06,210
That's "institutionalized."

797
01:00:06,419 --> 01:00:07,712
Shit.

798
01:00:07,921 --> 01:00:10,672
- I could never get like that.
- Oh, yeah?

799
01:00:11,548 --> 01:00:14,051
Wait till you've been here
as long as Brooks.

800
01:00:14,301 --> 01:00:15,845
Goddamn right.

801
01:00:18,431 --> 01:00:20,349
They send you here for life...

802
01:00:21,017 --> 01:00:23,353
...that's exactly what they take.

803
01:00:25,105 --> 01:00:27,107
Part that counts, anyway.

804
01:00:34,696 --> 01:00:37,659
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

805
01:00:38,826 --> 01:00:40,494
You go on now.

806
01:00:41,704 --> 01:00:43,205
You're free.

807
01:00:44,498 --> 01:00:46,041
You're free.

808
01:01:05,060 --> 01:01:06,728
Good luck, Brooksie.

809
01:01:44,725 --> 01:01:46,226
Dear fellas:

810
01:01:46,477 --> 01:01:50,689
I can't believe how fast things move
on the outside.

811
01:01:51,982 --> 01:01:54,651
Watch it, old-timer!
Want to get killed?

812
01:01:55,903 --> 01:01:59,406
I saw an automobile once
when I was a kid...

813
01:02:00,032 --> 01:02:02,451
...but now they're everywhere.

814
01:02:06,121 --> 01:02:10,459
The world went and got itself
in a big damn hurry.

815
01:02:26,265 --> 01:02:30,019
The parole board
got me into this halfway house...

816
01:02:30,311 --> 01:02:31,980
...called "The Brewer"...

817
01:02:32,188 --> 01:02:33,357
...and a job...

818
01:02:33,565 --> 01:02:36,526
...bagging groceries at the Food-Way.

819
01:02:38,070 --> 01:02:40,489
It's hard work and I try to keep up...

820
01:02:40,696 --> 01:02:43,075
...but my hands hurt most of the time.

821
01:02:43,367 --> 01:02:45,326
Make sure your man double-bags.

822
01:02:45,536 --> 01:02:47,579
Last time, the bottom near came out.

823
01:02:48,247 --> 01:02:51,166
Make sure you double-bag
like the lady says. Understand?

824
01:02:51,374 --> 01:02:52,751
Yes, sir. Surely will.

825
01:02:52,959 --> 01:02:56,462
I don't think the store manager
likes me very much.

826
01:02:59,508 --> 01:03:03,803
Sometimes after work,
I go to the park and feed the birds.

827
01:03:04,220 --> 01:03:05,722
I keep thinking...

828
01:03:05,972 --> 01:03:09,308
...Jake might just show up
and say hello.

829
01:03:09,892 --> 01:03:11,894
But he never does.

830
01:03:13,105 --> 01:03:17,984
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay
and making new friends.

831
01:03:21,571 --> 01:03:24,323
I have trouble sleeping at night.

832
01:03:24,615 --> 01:03:27,870
I have bad dreams like I'm falling.

833
01:03:28,162 --> 01:03:30,371
I wake up scared.

834
01:03:30,581 --> 01:03:34,834
Sometimes it takes me a while
to remember where I am.

835
01:03:36,335 --> 01:03:41,215
Maybe I should get a gun and rob
the Food-Way so they'd send me home.

836
01:03:41,549 --> 01:03:45,887
I could shoot the manager while
I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.

837
01:03:47,555 --> 01:03:51,517
I guess I'm too old
for that sort of nonsense anymore.

838
01:03:51,768 --> 01:03:53,519
I don't like it here.

839
01:03:53,729 --> 01:03:57,690
I'm tired of being afraid all the time.
I've decided...

840
01:03:58,566 --> 01:04:00,193
...not to stay.

841
01:04:11,120 --> 01:04:13,706
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...

842
01:04:13,915 --> 01:04:17,376
...not for an old crook like me.

843
01:05:19,856 --> 01:05:24,151
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss,
not for an old crook like me.

844
01:05:25,152 --> 01:05:28,990
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry
I put a knife to his throat.

845
01:05:29,197 --> 01:05:31,534
No hard feelings. Brooks."

846
01:05:42,003 --> 01:05:44,005
He should have died in here.

847
01:05:49,510 --> 01:05:50,928
What the fuck have you done?

848
01:05:51,136 --> 01:05:53,806
It's a goddamn mess,
I'll tell you that.

849
01:05:59,352 --> 01:06:03,065
- What's all this?
- You tell me. They're addressed to you.

850
01:06:04,358 --> 01:06:05,693
Take it.

851
01:06:14,202 --> 01:06:15,702
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:

852
01:06:16,870 --> 01:06:18,831
In response to your inquiries...

853
01:06:19,039 --> 01:06:23,294
...the state has allocated the enclosed
funds for your library project."

854
01:06:24,044 --> 01:06:25,880
This is $200.

855
01:06:26,088 --> 01:06:30,093
"In addition, the library district
has generously responded...

856
01:06:30,300 --> 01:06:32,845
...with a donation of used books
and sundries.

857
01:06:33,053 --> 01:06:37,182
We trust this will fill your needs.
We now consider the matter closed.

858
01:06:37,390 --> 01:06:39,226
Please stop sending us letters."

859
01:06:39,434 --> 01:06:42,104
Clear all this out
before the warden gets back.

860
01:06:42,355 --> 01:06:43,523
Yes, sir.

861
01:06:47,776 --> 01:06:48,944
Good for you, Andy.

862
01:06:51,906 --> 01:06:53,032
Wow!

863
01:06:54,241 --> 01:06:56,202
It only took six years.

864
01:06:57,744 --> 01:07:00,497
From now on, I'll write two
letters a week instead of one.

865
01:07:00,706 --> 01:07:04,042
I believe you're crazy enough.
Get this stuff out...

866
01:07:04,293 --> 01:07:05,127
...like he said.

867
01:07:05,336 --> 01:07:06,754
I've got to pinch a loaf.

868
01:07:06,921 --> 01:07:08,422
When I come back...

869
01:07:08,588 --> 01:07:10,383
...this is all gone, all right?

870
01:07:59,139 --> 01:08:00,515
Do you hear that?

871
01:09:09,250 --> 01:09:10,418
Dufresne!

872
01:09:12,963 --> 01:09:14,506
Andy, let me out!

873
01:09:21,387 --> 01:09:26,308
I have no idea to this day what those
two Italian ladies were singing about.

874
01:09:26,600 --> 01:09:28,854
Truth is, I don't want to know.

875
01:09:29,061 --> 01:09:31,522
Some things are best left unsaid.

876
01:09:35,109 --> 01:09:37,862
I like to think it was something
so beautiful...

877
01:09:38,071 --> 01:09:40,197
...it can't be expressed in words...

878
01:09:40,406 --> 01:09:43,285
...and makes your heart ache
because of it.

879
01:09:44,952 --> 01:09:47,456
I tell you, those voices soared...

880
01:09:47,748 --> 01:09:52,042
...higher and farther than anybody
in a gray place dares to dream.

881
01:09:52,251 --> 01:09:55,588
It was like a beautiful bird
flapped into our drab cage...

882
01:09:55,796 --> 01:09:58,592
...and made those walls dissolve away.

883
01:09:59,009 --> 01:10:01,218
And for the briefest of moments...

884
01:10:01,427 --> 01:10:04,388
...every last man at Shawshank
felt free.

885
01:10:06,974 --> 01:10:09,643
It pissed the warden off
something awful.

886
01:10:10,936 --> 01:10:11,937
Open the door.

887
01:10:14,857 --> 01:10:16,609
Open it up!

888
01:10:17,943 --> 01:10:20,654
Dufresne, open this door!

889
01:10:21,989 --> 01:10:23,199
Turn that off!

890
01:10:30,289 --> 01:10:32,708
I am warning you. Turn that off!

891
01:10:50,476 --> 01:10:51,977
You're mine now.

892
01:10:59,443 --> 01:11:02,655
Andy got two weeks in the hole
for that little stunt.

893
01:11:02,863 --> 01:11:04,447
On your feet.

894
01:11:05,658 --> 01:11:08,035
- Hey, look who's here.
- Maestro!

895
01:11:09,829 --> 01:11:13,457
You couldn't play something good, huh?
Like Hank Williams?

896
01:11:13,832 --> 01:11:16,627
They broke the door down
before I could take requests.

897
01:11:16,836 --> 01:11:19,964
- Was it worth two weeks?
- Easiest time I ever did.

898
01:11:20,171 --> 01:11:24,343
- No such thing as easy time in the hole.
- A week in the hole is like a year.

899
01:11:24,552 --> 01:11:27,846
- Damn straight.
- I had Mr. Mozart to keep me company.

900
01:11:28,055 --> 01:11:31,015
So they let you tote
that record player down there, huh?

901
01:11:33,476 --> 01:11:34,854
It was in here.

902
01:11:35,688 --> 01:11:36,897
In here.

903
01:11:38,023 --> 01:11:40,151
That's the beauty of music. They...

904
01:11:40,359 --> 01:11:42,695
...can't get that from you.

905
01:11:46,197 --> 01:11:48,576
Haven't you ever felt
that way about music?

906
01:11:50,368 --> 01:11:53,497
Well, I played a mean harmonica
as a younger man.

907
01:11:54,539 --> 01:11:56,250
Lost interest in it, though.

908
01:11:56,458 --> 01:11:58,042
Didn't make much sense in here.

909
01:11:58,377 --> 01:12:00,379
Here's where it makes the most sense.

910
01:12:00,920 --> 01:12:03,007
You need it so you don't forget.

911
01:12:03,548 --> 01:12:04,759
Forget?

912
01:12:05,133 --> 01:12:08,220
Forget that there are...

913
01:12:08,428 --> 01:12:09,888
...places...

914
01:12:10,389 --> 01:12:14,225
...in the world
that aren't made out of stone.

915
01:12:15,226 --> 01:12:16,686
There's something...

916
01:12:17,061 --> 01:12:18,439
...inside...

917
01:12:18,731 --> 01:12:20,690
...that they can't get to...

918
01:12:20,900 --> 01:12:22,234
...that they can't touch.

919
01:12:22,777 --> 01:12:24,236
That's yours.

920
01:12:25,737 --> 01:12:27,363
What are you talking about?

921
01:12:28,407 --> 01:12:29,617
Hope.

922
01:12:30,700 --> 01:12:32,036
Hope.

923
01:12:33,953 --> 01:12:35,956
Let me tell you something, my friend.

924
01:12:36,748 --> 01:12:39,084
Hope is a dangerous thing.

925
01:12:40,252 --> 01:12:42,588
Hope can drive a man insane.

926
01:12:43,297 --> 01:12:45,423
It's got no use on the inside.

927
01:12:45,633 --> 01:12:47,842
You'd better get used to that idea.

928
01:12:50,345 --> 01:12:51,847
Like Brooks did?

929
01:13:17,205 --> 01:13:18,206
Sit down.

930
01:13:23,545 --> 01:13:26,840
Says here that you've served
30 years of a life sentence.

931
01:13:28,007 --> 01:13:30,093
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

932
01:13:30,301 --> 01:13:31,511
Oh, yes, sir.

933
01:13:32,804 --> 01:13:34,139
Without a doubt.

934
01:13:35,307 --> 01:13:37,684
I can honestly say I'm a changed man.

935
01:13:39,686 --> 01:13:41,646
No danger to society here.

936
01:13:42,147 --> 01:13:43,689
God's honest truth.

937
01:13:46,276 --> 01:13:48,361
Absolutely rehabilitated.

938
01:13:58,371 --> 01:13:59,706
Thirty years.

939
01:14:01,666 --> 01:14:03,585
Jesus, when you say it like that...

940
01:14:04,419 --> 01:14:06,254
You wonder where it went.

941
01:14:08,672 --> 01:14:10,841
I wonder where 10 years went.

942
01:14:15,805 --> 01:14:16,848
Here.

943
01:14:17,265 --> 01:14:20,018
A little parole rejection present.

944
01:14:21,269 --> 01:14:22,978
Go ahead and open it.

945
01:14:24,105 --> 01:14:26,107
Went through one of your competitors.

946
01:14:26,315 --> 01:14:29,444
I hope you don't mind.
I wanted it to be a surprise.

947
01:14:39,496 --> 01:14:40,997
It's very pretty.

948
01:14:42,707 --> 01:14:43,916
Thank you.

949
01:14:46,461 --> 01:14:47,961
You going to play it?

950
01:14:52,509 --> 01:14:53,759
No.

951
01:14:57,388 --> 01:14:58,806
Not right now.

952
01:15:16,491 --> 01:15:17,574
Roll in!

953
01:15:53,778 --> 01:15:54,987
Lights out!

954
01:16:29,605 --> 01:16:31,732
Andy was as good as his word.

955
01:16:32,107 --> 01:16:34,902
He wrote two letters a week
instead of one.

956
01:16:36,946 --> 01:16:41,033
In 1959, the state senate
finally clued in to the fact...

957
01:16:41,284 --> 01:16:44,411
...they couldn't buy him off
with just a $200 check.

958
01:16:44,620 --> 01:16:48,916
Appropriations Committee
voted an annual payment of $500...

959
01:16:49,124 --> 01:16:51,043
...just to shut him up.

960
01:16:51,251 --> 01:16:54,213
And you'd be amazed how far
Andy could stretch it.

961
01:16:54,420 --> 01:16:57,382
He made deals with book clubs,
charity groups.

962
01:16:57,591 --> 01:17:00,343
He bought remaindered books
by the pound...

963
01:17:00,844 --> 01:17:02,387
Treasure Island.

964
01:17:02,930 --> 01:17:04,264
Robert Louis-

965
01:17:04,431 --> 01:17:05,474
Stevenson.

966
01:17:05,681 --> 01:17:07,059
Fiction, adventure.

967
01:17:09,603 --> 01:17:10,646
What's next?

968
01:17:10,854 --> 01:17:13,899
I got here Auto Repair...

969
01:17:14,649 --> 01:17:15,817
...and Soap Carving.

970
01:17:16,026 --> 01:17:19,238
Trade skills and hobbies.
Under "Educational," behind you.

971
01:17:19,446 --> 01:17:21,323
Count of Monte Crisco.

972
01:17:21,782 --> 01:17:24,118
That's "Cristo," you dumb shit.

973
01:17:25,201 --> 01:17:26,202
By Alexandree...

974
01:17:26,662 --> 01:17:27,913
...Dum-ass.

975
01:17:28,288 --> 01:17:29,289
Dumb ass.

976
01:17:31,625 --> 01:17:32,668
Dumb ass?

977
01:17:35,586 --> 01:17:37,548
Dumas. Know what that's about?

978
01:17:39,799 --> 01:17:41,801
You'd like it.
It's about a prison break.

979
01:17:41,968 --> 01:17:45,889
We ought to file that
under "Educational" too, oughtn't we?

980
01:17:46,765 --> 01:17:50,853
The rest of us did our best
to pitch in when and where we could.

981
01:17:51,437 --> 01:17:53,187
By the year Kennedy was shot...

982
01:17:53,439 --> 01:17:57,943
...Andy had transformed a storage room
smelling of turpentine...

983
01:17:58,235 --> 01:18:01,320
...into the best prison library
in New England...

984
01:18:02,029 --> 01:18:04,992
...complete with a fine selection
of Hank Williams.

985
01:18:12,332 --> 01:18:14,292
That was also when Warden Norton...

986
01:18:14,501 --> 01:18:17,421
...instituted his famous
"Inside Out" program.

987
01:18:17,879 --> 01:18:19,964
You may remember reading about it.

988
01:18:20,174 --> 01:18:23,302
It made the papers
and got his picture in Look magazine.

989
01:18:23,509 --> 01:18:24,803
It's no free ride...

990
01:18:25,011 --> 01:18:28,223
.. but rather a genuine
progressive advance...

991
01:18:28,431 --> 01:18:30,933
...in corrections and rehabilitation.

992
01:18:31,268 --> 01:18:33,811
Our inmates, properly supervised...

993
01:18:34,021 --> 01:18:36,647
...will be put to work
outside these walls...

994
01:18:36,856 --> 01:18:40,401
...performing all manner
of public service.

995
01:18:40,693 --> 01:18:42,904
These men can learn the value...

996
01:18:43,113 --> 01:18:46,908
...of an honest day's labor and
provide a service to the community...

997
01:18:47,116 --> 01:18:51,829
...at a bare minimum of expense
to Mr. and Mrs. John Q. Taxpayer.

998
01:18:52,246 --> 01:18:54,582
Of course he didn't tell the press...

999
01:18:54,791 --> 01:18:58,252
...that "bare minimum of expense"
is a fairly loose term.

1000
01:18:58,461 --> 01:19:01,506
There are 100 different ways
to skim off the top.

1001
01:19:01,714 --> 01:19:04,175
Men, materials, you name it.

1002
01:19:04,550 --> 01:19:07,428
And oh, my Lord,
how the money rolled in!

1003
01:19:07,637 --> 01:19:10,181
At this rate,
you'll put me out of business.

1004
01:19:10,389 --> 01:19:14,811
With this pool of slave labor,
you can underbid any contractor in town.

1005
01:19:15,394 --> 01:19:18,357
We're providing
a valuable community service.

1006
01:19:18,564 --> 01:19:22,193
That's fine for the papers,
but I've got a family to feed.

1007
01:19:24,904 --> 01:19:26,406
We go back a long way.

1008
01:19:27,740 --> 01:19:32,663
I need this highway contract. I don't
get it and I go under. That's a fact.

1009
01:19:33,579 --> 01:19:35,373
You have some of this fine pie...

1010
01:19:35,581 --> 01:19:38,918
...my missus made for you.
You think about that.

1011
01:19:47,218 --> 01:19:49,887
I wouldn't worry too much
about this contract.

1012
01:19:50,137 --> 01:19:53,224
I already got my boys
committed elsewhere.

1013
01:19:55,184 --> 01:19:58,228
You be sure and thank Maisie
for this fine pie.

1014
01:19:59,355 --> 01:20:01,524
And behind every shady deal...

1015
01:20:01,858 --> 01:20:04,485
...behind every dollar earned...

1016
01:20:04,777 --> 01:20:07,822
...there was Andy, keeping the books.

