What you got?

1262
01:34:38,396 --> 01:34:39,731
Board of Education.

1263
01:34:39,939 --> 01:34:41,441
That son of a bitch mailed it.

1264
01:34:41,649 --> 01:34:45,611
You going to open it or stand there
with your thumb up your butt?

1265
01:34:45,820 --> 01:34:47,989
Thumb up my butt sounds better.

1266
01:34:48,488 --> 01:34:51,325
Skeets, come on.
Give me that, you shithead.

1267
01:34:52,160 --> 01:34:53,494
Floyd, come on.

1268
01:34:58,958 --> 01:35:01,335
Will you throw that away, please?

1269
01:35:06,966 --> 01:35:08,676
Well, shit.

1270
01:35:21,355 --> 01:35:24,150
The kid passed. C + average.

1271
01:35:24,358 --> 01:35:26,485
Thought you'd like to know.

1272
01:35:42,710 --> 01:35:44,170
Warden wants to talk.

1273
01:35:57,892 --> 01:35:58,975
Out here?

1274
01:35:59,185 --> 01:36:01,396
That's what the man said.

1275
01:36:17,537 --> 01:36:18,538
Warden?

1276
01:36:28,548 --> 01:36:32,592
I'm asking you to keep this conversation
just between us.

1277
01:36:34,094 --> 01:36:36,388
I feel awkward enough as it is.

1278
01:36:54,824 --> 01:36:56,908
We got a situation here.

1279
01:36:57,784 --> 01:36:59,871
I think you can appreciate that.

1280
01:37:00,078 --> 01:37:01,288
Yes, sir.

1281
01:37:01,580 --> 01:37:02,956
I sure can.

1282
01:37:03,248 --> 01:37:07,252
I tell you, son, this thing really
came along and knocked my wind out.

1283
01:37:08,754 --> 01:37:11,298
It's got me up nights.
That's the truth.

1284
01:37:13,593 --> 01:37:15,427
The right thing to do...

1285
01:37:17,095 --> 01:37:20,808
...sometimes it's hard to know
what that is.

1286
01:37:21,808 --> 01:37:23,269
Do you understand?

1287
01:37:25,562 --> 01:37:27,147
I need your help, son.

1288
01:37:28,607 --> 01:37:30,777
If I'm going to move on this...

1289
01:37:31,109 --> 01:37:34,279
...there can't be
the least little shred of doubt.

1290
01:37:34,988 --> 01:37:36,073
I have to know...

1291
01:37:36,281 --> 01:37:38,909
...if what you told Dufresne
was the truth.

1292
01:37:39,117 --> 01:37:40,243
Yes, sir.

1293
01:37:40,451 --> 01:37:41,661
Absolutely.

1294
01:37:42,162 --> 01:37:45,165
Would you be willing to swear
before a judge and jury...

1295
01:37:45,373 --> 01:37:47,375
...with your hand on the Good Book...

1296
01:37:47,584 --> 01:37:50,253
...and take an oath
before Almighty God himself?

1297
01:37:50,462 --> 01:37:52,255
Just give me that chance.

1298
01:37:56,510 --> 01:37:57,844
That's what I thought.

1299
01:38:44,933 --> 01:38:46,852
I'm sure by now you've heard.

1300
01:38:48,602 --> 01:38:49,645
Terrible thing.

1301
01:38:51,230 --> 01:38:52,733
A man that young...

1302
01:38:53,066 --> 01:38:55,652
...less than a year to go,
trying to escape.

1303
01:38:56,194 --> 01:38:58,697
Broke Captain Hadley's heart
to shoot him.

1304
01:38:59,406 --> 01:39:00,906
Truly, it did.

1305
01:39:03,909 --> 01:39:06,370
We just have to put it behind us.

1306
01:39:08,039 --> 01:39:09,249
Move on.

1307
01:39:10,875 --> 01:39:12,377
I'm done.

1308
01:39:13,670 --> 01:39:15,297
Everything stops.

1309
01:39:17,256 --> 01:39:19,593
Get someone else to run your scams.

1310
01:39:20,886 --> 01:39:22,720
Nothing stops.

1311
01:39:24,055 --> 01:39:25,223
Nothing.

1312
01:39:28,601 --> 01:39:31,730
Or you will do
the hardest time there is.

1313
01:39:32,104 --> 01:39:34,440
No more protection from the guards.

1314
01:39:34,649 --> 01:39:39,570
I'll pull you out of that 1-bunk Hilton
and cast you down with the sodomites.

1315
01:39:40,946 --> 01:39:43,407
You'll think you've been
fucked by a train.

1316
01:39:44,784 --> 01:39:46,285
And the library?

1317
01:39:46,952 --> 01:39:47,953
Gone.

1318
01:39:48,579 --> 01:39:51,123
Sealed off, brick by brick.

1319
01:39:51,624 --> 01:39:54,251
We'll have us a little
book barbecue in the yard.

1320
01:39:54,460 --> 01:39:56,588
They'll see the flames for miles.

1321
01:39:56,796 --> 01:39:59,633
We'll dance around it like wild Injuns.

1322
01:40:00,926 --> 01:40:03,928
You understand me? Catching my drift?

1323
01:40:07,640 --> 01:40:09,517
Or am I being obtuse?

1324
01:40:21,320 --> 01:40:23,948
Give him another month
to think about it.

1325
01:41:10,702 --> 01:41:13,748
My wife used to say
I'm a hard man to know.

1326
01:41:14,540 --> 01:41:16,375
Like a closed book.

1327
01:41:17,209 --> 01:41:19,210
Complained about it all the time.

1328
01:41:20,171 --> 01:41:21,714
She was beautiful.

1329
01:41:24,132 --> 01:41:25,676
God, I loved her.

1330
01:41:29,388 --> 01:41:31,599
I didn't know how
to show it, that's all.

1331
01:41:34,350 --> 01:41:36,020
I killed her, Red.

1332
01:41:37,897 --> 01:41:39,690
I didn't pull the trigger...

1333
01:41:41,108 --> 01:41:42,860
...but I drove her away.

1334
01:41:44,360 --> 01:41:47,031
That's why she died, because of me...

1335
01:41:47,238 --> 01:41:48,616
...the way I am.

1336
01:41:57,624 --> 01:41:59,460
That don't make you a murderer.

1337
01:42:02,837 --> 01:42:04,589
Bad husband, maybe.

1338
01:42:08,260 --> 01:42:11,513
Feel bad about it if you want,
but you didn't pull the trigger.

1339
01:42:11,722 --> 01:42:13,056
No, I didn't.

1340
01:42:13,432 --> 01:42:15,392
Somebody else did.

1341
01:42:16,602 --> 01:42:18,728
And I wound up in here.

1342
01:42:21,189 --> 01:42:22,774
Bad luck, I guess.

1343
01:42:27,987 --> 01:42:29,447
It floats around.

1344
01:42:30,448 --> 01:42:32,700
It's got to land on somebody.

1345
01:42:33,618 --> 01:42:35,495
It was my turn, that's all.

1346
01:42:36,204 --> 01:42:38,957
I was in the path of the tornado.

1347
01:42:44,922 --> 01:42:48,883
I just didn't expect the storm
would last as long as it has.

1348
01:42:53,221 --> 01:42:54,931
Think you'll ever get out of here?

1349
01:42:56,141 --> 01:42:57,183
Me?

1350
01:43:00,145 --> 01:43:01,146
Yeah.

1351
01:43:02,480 --> 01:43:04,816
One day, when I got
a long, white beard...

1352
01:43:04,983 --> 01:43:08,153
...and two or three marbles
rolling around upstairs.

1353
01:43:10,196 --> 01:43:11,823
I tell you where I'd go.

1354
01:43:13,324 --> 01:43:14,951
Zihuatanejo.

1355
01:43:15,827 --> 01:43:17,036
Say what?

1356
01:43:17,328 --> 01:43:19,164
Zihuatanejo.

1357
01:43:20,123 --> 01:43:21,791
It's in Mexico.

1358
01:43:23,168 --> 01:43:25,295
A little place on the Pacific Ocean.

1359
01:43:26,421 --> 01:43:29,215
You know what the Mexicans say
about the Pacific?

1360
01:43:31,009 --> 01:43:33,011
They say it has no memory.

1361
01:43:35,013 --> 01:43:37,640
That's where I want to live
the rest of my life.

1362
01:43:39,309 --> 01:43:41,811
A warm place with no memory.

1363
01:43:45,022 --> 01:43:46,983
Open up a little hotel...

1364
01:43:48,693 --> 01:43:50,153
...right on the beach.

1365
01:43:50,779 --> 01:43:52,989
Buy some worthless old boat...

1366
01:43:53,531 --> 01:43:55,158
...and fix it up new.

1367
01:43:57,869 --> 01:43:59,120
Take my guests out...

1368
01:43:59,954 --> 01:44:01,331
...charter fishing.

1369
01:44:05,168 --> 01:44:06,878
Zihuatanejo.

1370
01:44:10,423 --> 01:44:14,302
In a place like that, I could use
a man that knows how to get things.

1371
01:44:20,849 --> 01:44:23,686
I don't think I could make it
on the outside.

1372
01:44:30,359 --> 01:44:32,403
I been in here most of my life.

1373
01:44:33,862 --> 01:44:35,615
I'm an institutional man now.

1374
01:44:36,533 --> 01:44:38,243
Just like Brooks was.

1375
01:44:39,743 --> 01:44:41,413
You underestimate yourself.

1376
01:44:41,996 --> 01:44:43,581
I don't think so.

1377
01:44:47,418 --> 01:44:51,381
In here I'm the guy who can get things
for you, sure, but...

1378
01:44:52,132 --> 01:44:54,675
...outside all you need
is the Yellow Pages.

1379
01:44:54,884 --> 01:44:57,094
Hell, I wouldn't know
where to begin.

1380
01:44:59,263 --> 01:45:00,890
Pacific Ocean?

1381
01:45:01,265 --> 01:45:02,517
Shit.

1382
01:45:02,891 --> 01:45:05,060
Scare me to death,
something that big.

1383
01:45:05,270 --> 01:45:06,563
Not me.

1384
01:45:07,771 --> 01:45:10,566
I didn't shoot my wife,
and I didn't shoot her lover.

1385
01:45:12,276 --> 01:45:15,530
Whatever mistakes I made,
I've paid for them and then some.

1386
01:45:16,572 --> 01:45:18,073
That hotel, that boat...

1387
01:45:19,826 --> 01:45:22,077
I don't think that's too much to ask.

1388
01:45:26,957 --> 01:45:29,418
You shouldn't be doing this to yourself.

1389
01:45:29,626 --> 01:45:31,628
This is just shitty pipe dreams.

1390
01:45:32,087 --> 01:45:34,548
Mexico is way down there
and you're in here...

1391
01:45:34,758 --> 01:45:36,301
...and that's the way it is.

1392
01:45:36,633 --> 01:45:39,470
Yeah, right.
That's the way it is.

1393
01:45:40,971 --> 01:45:43,391
It's down there and I'm in here.

1394
01:45:45,977 --> 01:45:48,687
I guess it comes down
to a simple choice.

1395
01:45:51,607 --> 01:45:53,108
Get busy living...

1396
01:45:54,485 --> 01:45:56,487
...or get busy dying.

1397
01:46:08,624 --> 01:46:11,335
If you ever get out of here,
do me a favor.

1398
01:46:11,543 --> 01:46:13,796
Sure, Andy. Anything.

1399
01:46:15,672 --> 01:46:19,551
There's a big hayfield up near Buxton.
You know where Buxton is?

1400
01:46:21,011 --> 01:46:24,139
- A lot of hayfields up there.
- One in particular.

1401
01:46:24,348 --> 01:46:28,310
It's got a long rock wall
with a big oak tree at the north end.

1402
01:46:28,519 --> 01:46:31,356
It's like something
out of a Robert Frost poem.

1403
01:46:32,314 --> 01:46:34,816
It's where I asked my wife to marry me.

1404
01:46:36,193 --> 01:46:38,320
We went there for a picnic...

1405
01:46:38,695 --> 01:46:40,823
...and made love under that oak...

1406
01:46:41,490 --> 01:46:43,700
...and I asked and she said yes.

1407
01:46:47,704 --> 01:46:49,540
Promise me, Red.

1408
01:46:50,374 --> 01:46:51,999
If you ever get out...

1409
01:46:52,209 --> 01:46:53,711
...find that spot.

1410
01:46:54,878 --> 01:46:59,717
At the base of that wall, there's a rock
that has no earthly business in Maine.

1411
01:47:00,884 --> 01:47:03,887
Piece of black, volcanic glass.

1412
01:47:06,557 --> 01:47:09,226
Something's buried under it
I want you to have.

1413
01:47:10,018 --> 01:47:11,227
What, Andy?

1414
01:47:11,687 --> 01:47:13,396
What's buried under there?

1415
01:47:15,023 --> 01:47:16,900
You'll have to pry it up...

1416
01:47:17,067 --> 01:47:18,360
...to see.

1417
01:47:24,241 --> 01:47:26,201
No, I'm telling you. The guy is...

1418
01:47:26,869 --> 01:47:28,579
He's talking funny.

1419
01:47:29,704 --> 01:47:31,373
I'm really worried about him.

1420
01:47:31,790 --> 01:47:33,250
Let's keep an eye on him.

1421
01:47:33,417 --> 01:47:36,712
That's fine during the day,
but at night he's all alone.

1422
01:47:38,130 --> 01:47:39,255
Oh, Lord.

1423
01:47:40,591 --> 01:47:41,424
What?

1424
01:47:42,926 --> 01:47:45,720
Andy come down
to the loading dock today.

1425
01:47:45,929 --> 01:47:48,015
He asked me for a length of rope.

1426
01:47:48,223 --> 01:47:49,057
Rope?

1427
01:47:49,266 --> 01:47:50,893
Six feet long.

1428
01:47:51,143 --> 01:47:52,518
And you gave it to him.

1429
01:47:53,394 --> 01:47:55,189
Sure. Why wouldn't I?

1430
01:47:55,396 --> 01:47:56,940
Jesus! Heywood.

1431
01:47:57,565 --> 01:47:59,526
How was I supposed to know?

1432
01:47:59,734 --> 01:48:01,278
Remember Brooks Hatlen?

1433
01:48:03,280 --> 01:48:05,239
Andy would never do that.

1434
01:48:05,823 --> 01:48:06,909
Never.

1435
01:48:08,952 --> 01:48:10,286
I don't know.

1436
01:48:13,123 --> 01:48:15,166
Every man has his breaking point.

1437
01:48:17,502 --> 01:48:19,755
Lickety-split.
Want to get home.

1438
01:48:20,088 --> 01:48:21,839
Just about finished, sir.

1439
01:48:38,982 --> 01:48:40,608
Three deposits tonight.

1440
01:48:48,574 --> 01:48:50,493
Get my stuff down to the laundry.

1441
01:48:50,661 --> 01:48:52,286
And shine my shoes.

1442
01:48:52,495 --> 01:48:55,456
- I want them looking like mirrors.
- Yes, sir.

1443
01:49:00,962 --> 01:49:02,422
It's good having you back.

1444
01:49:03,339 --> 01:49:05,216
Place wasn't the same without you.

1445
01:49:52,096 --> 01:49:53,181
Lights out!

1446
01:50:26,004 --> 01:50:28,549
I've had some long nights in stir.

1447
01:50:29,092 --> 01:50:31,719
Alone in the dark
with nothing but your thoughts...

1448
01:50:31,927 --> 01:50:34,597
...time can draw out like a blade.

1449
01:50:39,936 --> 01:50:42,939
That was the longest night of my life.

1450
01:50:58,787 --> 01:50:59,955
Give me a count!

1451
01:51:04,460 --> 01:51:07,295
Tier 3 south, clear!

1452
01:51:10,465 --> 01:51:13,594
Man missing on tier 2, cell 245!

1453
01:51:13,802 --> 01:51:14,887
Dufresne!

1454
01:51:15,429 --> 01:51:17,848
Come out. You're holding up the show!

1455
01:51:20,977 --> 01:51:24,397
Don't make me come down
or I'll thump your skull for you!

1456
01:51:31,987 --> 01:51:35,825
Damn it, you're putting me behind!
I got a schedule to keep.

1457
01:51:35,992 --> 01:51:39,287
You'd better be sick or dead in there.
I shit you not!

1458
01:51:39,494 --> 01:51:40,829
You hear me?

1459
01:51:46,961 --> 01:51:49,046
Oh, my Holy God.

1460
01:52:06,022 --> 01:52:08,607
I want every man
on this cellblock questioned.

1461
01:52:09,024 --> 01:52:11,610
- Start with that friend of his.
- Who?

1462
01:52:14,196 --> 01:52:15,739
Open 237.

1463
01:52:19,242 --> 01:52:22,913
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"?
Don't say that to me.

1464
01:52:23,790 --> 01:52:25,123
Don't tell me that again.

1465
01:52:25,332 --> 01:52:26,333
But sir, he wasn't.

1466
01:52:26,583 --> 01:52:30,045
I can see that, Haig!
Think I'm blind?

1467
01:52:30,712 --> 01:52:32,130
Is that what you're saying?

1468
01:52:32,339 --> 01:52:35,008
- Am I blind, Haig?
- No, sir!

1469
01:52:35,884 --> 01:52:38,387
What about you. You blind?

1470
01:52:38,887 --> 01:52:41,473
- Tell me what this is.
- Last night's count.

1471
01:52:41,681 --> 01:52:44,976
You see Dufresne's name there?
I sure do. Right there.

1472
01:52:45,185 --> 01:52:46,520
"Dufresne."

1473
01:52:48,188 --> 01:52:49,647
He was in his cell...

1474
01:52:49,898 --> 01:52:50,857
...at lights out.

1475
01:52:51,066 --> 01:52:53,318
Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.

1476
01:52:54,361 --> 01:52:55,986
I want him found.

1477
01:52:56,196 --> 01:52:59,658
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1478
01:52:59,907 --> 01:53:01,076
Yes, sir.

1479
01:53:02,076 --> 01:53:04,370
Let's go. Move your butts.

1480
01:53:07,749 --> 01:53:08,750
Stand.

1481
01:53:10,210 --> 01:53:11,253
Well?

1482
01:53:14,715 --> 01:53:15,674
Well, what?

1483
01:53:15,923 --> 01:53:19,385
I see you two all the time.
You're thick as thieves, you are.

1484
01:53:20,428 --> 01:53:21,930
He must have said something.

1485
01:53:22,681 --> 01:53:24,224
No, sir, Warden.

1486
01:53:24,598 --> 01:53:25,559
Not a word.

1487
01:53:27,394 --> 01:53:29,937
Lord, it's a miracle!

1488
01:53:30,564 --> 01:53:33,107
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1489
01:53:33,775 --> 01:53:34,943
Nothing left...

1490
01:53:35,777 --> 01:53:38,530
...but some damn rocks
on a windowsill.

1491
01:53:38,738 --> 01:53:41,450
And that cupcake on the wall.
Let's ask her.

1492
01:53:41,657 --> 01:53:43,410
Maybe she knows.

1493
01:53:43,659 --> 01:53:46,412
What say there, fuzzy-britches?
Feel like talking?

1494
01:53:47,830 --> 01:53:49,123
Guess not.

1495
01:53:49,707 --> 01:53:51,917
Why should she be any different?

1496
01:53:52,961 --> 01:53:54,628
This is a conspiracy.

1497
01:53:55,297 --> 01:53:57,089
That's what this is.

1498
01:53:57,716 --> 01:54:01,427
One big, damn conspiracy!

1499
01:54:01,719 --> 01:54:03,721
And everyone's in on it!

1500
01:54:04,346 --> 01:54:05,515
Including her!

1501
01:54:40,549 --> 01:54:42,259
In 1966...

1502
01:54:42,468 --> 01:54:44,846
...Andy Dufresne escaped...

1503
01:54:45,054 --> 01:54:46,639
...from Shawshank Prison.

1504
01:54:48,849 --> 01:54:51,435
All they found
was a muddy set of prison clothes...

1505
01:54:52,062 --> 01:54:53,604
...a bar of soap...

1506
01:54:53,813 --> 01:54:55,356
...and an old rock hammer...

1507
01:54:55,564 --> 01:54:58,025
...damn near worn down to the nub.

1508
01:55:02,530 --> 01:55:07,326
I had thought it'd take a man 600 years
to tunnel through the wall with it.

1509
01:55:07,953 --> 01:55:10,579
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

1510
01:55:28,890 --> 01:55:31,183
Oh, Andy loved geology.

1511
01:55:31,934 --> 01:55:35,105
I imagine it appealed to his
meticulous nature.

1512
01:55:35,521 --> 01:55:37,356
An ice age here...

1513
01:55:37,773 --> 01:55:40,276
...million years
of mountain building there.

1514
01:55:41,277 --> 01:55:44,113
Geology is the study
of pressure and time.

1515
01:55:44,947 --> 01:55:46,948
That's all it takes, really.

1516
01:55:47,700 --> 01:55:48,784
Pressure...

1517
01:55:49,410 --> 01:55:50,702
...and time.

1518
01:55:52,038 --> 01:55:54,081
That and a big goddamn poster.

1519
01:55:58,127 --> 01:55:59,085
Like I said...

1520
01:55:59,587 --> 01:56:03,548
...in prison, a man will do anything
to keep his mind occupied.

1521
01:56:06,385 --> 01:56:11,182
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting
his wall out into the exercise yard...

1522
01:56:11,724 --> 01:56:13,642
...a handful at a time.

1523
01:56:14,935 --> 01:56:17,021
I guess after Tommy was killed...

1524
01:56:17,229 --> 01:56:20,191
...Andy decided
he'd been here long enough.

1525
01:56:20,399 --> 01:56:22,943
Lickety-split.
I want to get home.

1526
01:56:23,694 --> 01:56:25,738
I'm just about finished, sir.

1527
01:56:47,175 --> 01:56:49,136
Three deposits tonight.

1528
01:56:56,434 --> 01:56:58,728
Andy did like he was told.

1529
01:56:58,938 --> 01:57:02,400
Buffed those shoes
to a high mirror-shine.

1530
01:57:06,111 --> 01:57:08,405
The guards simply didn't notice.

1531
01:57:08,696 --> 01:57:10,156
Neither did I.

1532
01:57:10,366 --> 01:57:11,908
I mean, seriously...

1533
01:57:12,118 --> 01:57:15,121
...how often do you really look
at a man's shoes?

1534
01:59:18,660 --> 01:59:21,830
Andy crawled to freedom
through 500 yards...

1535
01:59:22,079 --> 01:59:25,416
...of shit-smelling foulness
I can't even imagine.

1536
01:59:26,417 --> 01:59:28,752
Or maybe I just don't want to.

1537
01:59:33,133 --> 01:59:35,509
Five hundred yards.

1538
01:59:36,010 --> 01:59:39,097
That's the length
of five football fields.

1539
01:59:39,722 --> 01:59:42,267
Just shy of half a mile.

1540
02:00:37,529 --> 02:00:42,117
The next morning, right about the time
Raquel was spilling her secret...

1541
02:00:42,409 --> 02:00:45,245
...a man nobody ever
laid eyes on before...

1542
02:00:45,497 --> 02:00:48,082
...strolled into
the Maine National Bank.

1543
02:00:48,666 --> 02:00:51,835
Until that moment,
he didn't exist.

1544
02:00:52,378 --> 02:00:54,756
- Except on paper.
- May I help you?

1545
02:00:55,173 --> 02:00:57,091
He had all the proper ID...

1546
02:00:57,299 --> 02:01:01,011
...driver's license, birth certificate,
Social Security card...

1547
02:01:01,428 --> 02:01:03,972
And the signature
was a spot-on match.

1548
02:01:04,181 --> 02:01:07,267
I must say I'm sorry
to be losing your business.

1549
02:01:07,476 --> 02:01:09,186
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1550
02:01:10,020 --> 02:01:11,105
Thank you.

1551
02:01:11,772 --> 02:01:12,940
I'm sure I will.

1552
02:01:13,857 --> 02:01:17,194
Here's your cashier's check, sir.
Will there be anything else?

1553
02:01:17,403 --> 02:01:18,362
Please.

1554
02:01:18,946 --> 02:01:21,448
Would you add this
to your outgoing mail?

1555
02:01:21,949 --> 02:01:23,158
I'd be happy to.

1556
02:01:24,952 --> 02:01:26,286
Good day, sir.

1557
02:01:27,246 --> 02:01:31,667
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks
in the Portland area that morning.

1558
02:01:32,126 --> 02:01:33,711
All told, he blew town...

1559
02:01:33,919 --> 02:01:38,757
...with better than $370,000
of Warden Norton's money.

1560
02:01:39,466 --> 02:01:42,219
Severance pay for 19 years.

1561
02:01:49,476 --> 02:01:51,687
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

1562
02:02:44,530 --> 02:02:47,493
Byron Hadley?
You have the right to remain silent.

1563
02:02:47,743 --> 02:02:52,163
If you give up this right, anything you
say can be held against you in court.

1564
02:02:52,622 --> 02:02:57,085
I wasn't there to see, but I hear
Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

1565
02:02:57,294 --> 02:02:58,754
...when they took him away.

1566
02:03:04,676 --> 02:03:08,054
Norton had no intention
of going that quietly.

1567
02:03:23,904 --> 02:03:24,738
Samuel Norton.

1568
02:03:25,530 --> 02:03:27,990
We have a warrant
for your arrest. Open up.

1569
02:03:32,705 --> 02:03:33,830
Open the door.

1570
02:03:34,372 --> 02:03:35,623
I'm not sure which key.

1571
02:03:45,758 --> 02:03:47,720
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1572
02:03:59,230 --> 02:04:02,650
I like to think the last thing
that went through his head...

1573
02:04:02,900 --> 02:04:04,486
...other than that bullet...

1574
02:04:04,694 --> 02:04:09,115
...was to wonder how the hell
Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

1575
02:04:11,617 --> 02:04:15,079
Not long after the warden
deprived us of his company...

1576
02:04:15,371 --> 02:04:17,415
...I got a postcard in the mail.

1577
02:04:18,917 --> 02:04:21,711
It was blank,
but the postmark said...

1578
02:04:21,919 --> 02:04:24,047
...Fort Hancock, Texas.

1579
02:04:24,589 --> 02:04:25,965
Fort Hancock...

1580
02:04:26,257 --> 02:04:27,967
...right on the border.

1581
02:04:28,384 --> 02:04:30,344
That's where Andy crossed.

1582
02:04:30,928 --> 02:04:35,058
When I picture him heading south
in his own car with the top down...

1583
02:04:35,433 --> 02:04:37,643
...it always makes me laugh.

1584
02:04:39,479 --> 02:04:41,064
Andy Dufresne...

1585
02:04:41,439 --> 02:04:43,441
...who crawled through
a river of shit...

1586
02:04:43,649 --> 02:04:46,069
...and came out clean
on the other side.

1587
02:04:46,903 --> 02:04:48,236
Andy Dufresne...

1588
02:04:49,072 --> 02:04:50,656
...headed for the Pacific.

1589
02:04:53,618 --> 02:04:55,787
Hadley's got him
by the throat, right?

1590
02:04:55,995 --> 02:04:59,790
He says, "I believe this boy's
about to have himself an accident."

1591
02:04:59,999 --> 02:05:02,877
Those of us who knew him best
talk about him often.

1592
02:05:03,543 --> 02:05:05,254
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

1593
02:05:05,463 --> 02:05:08,424
"My friends could use
a couple of beers."

1594
02:05:08,757 --> 02:05:10,426
And he got it!

1595
02:05:11,635 --> 02:05:14,055
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

1596
02:05:14,305 --> 02:05:15,765
...Andy being gone.

1597
02:05:16,474 --> 02:05:20,602
I have to remind myself that
some birds aren't meant to be caged.

1598
02:05:21,062 --> 02:05:23,106
Their feathers are just too bright.

1599
02:05:24,816 --> 02:05:26,567
And when they fly away...

1600
02:05:26,984 --> 02:05:31,406
...the part of you that knows it was
a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

1601
02:05:32,490 --> 02:05:33,740
But still...

1602
02:05:34,199 --> 02:05:38,538
...the place you live in is that much
more drab and empty that they're gone.

1603
02:05:42,750 --> 02:05:45,127
I guess I just miss my friend.

1604
02:06:09,818 --> 02:06:10,736
Please sit down.

1605
02:06:16,576 --> 02:06:18,161
Ellis Boyd Redding...

1606
02:06:18,702 --> 02:06:21,955
...your files say you've served
40 years of a life sentence.

1607
02:06:22,748 --> 02:06:24,875
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1608
02:06:26,752 --> 02:06:28,336
Rehabilitated?

1609
02:06:30,380 --> 02:06:32,257
Well, now, let me see.

1610
02:06:33,258 --> 02:06:35,594
I don't have any idea
what that means.

1611
02:06:37,721 --> 02:06:39,974
It means you're ready
to rejoin society-

1612
02:06:40,558 --> 02:06:42,852
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1613
02:06:45,062 --> 02:06:47,022
To me it's just a made-up word.

1614
02:06:48,398 --> 02:06:50,692
A politician's word so that...

1615
02:06:51,151 --> 02:06:54,697
...young fellas like yourself
can wear a suit and a tie...

1616
02:06:55,155 --> 02:06:56,740
...and have a job.

1617
02:06:58,743 --> 02:07:00,827
What do you really want to know?

1618
02:07:01,578 --> 02:07:03,580
Am I sorry for what I did?

1619
02:07:03,997 --> 02:07:05,165
Well, are you?

1620
02:07:07,084 --> 02:07:09,878
There's not a day goes by
I don't feel regret.

1621
02:07:11,254 --> 02:07:14,716
Not because I'm in here
or because you think I should.

1622
02:07:18,220 --> 02:07:20,764
I look back on the way I was then...

1623
02:07:22,933 --> 02:07:24,059
...a young...

1624
02:07:25,185 --> 02:07:28,688
...stupid kid who committed
that terrible crime.

1625
02:07:31,691 --> 02:07:33,402
I want to talk to him.

1626
02:07:35,320 --> 02:07:37,781
I want to try
and talk some sense to him.

1627
02:07:38,532 --> 02:07:40,450
Tell him the way things are.

1628
02:07:42,577 --> 02:07:43,995
But I can't.

1629
02:07:46,206 --> 02:07:48,208
That kid's long gone...

1630
02:07:49,418 --> 02:07:52,170
...and this old man is all that's left.

1631
02:07:53,588 --> 02:07:55,048
I got to live with that.

1632
02:07:56,425 --> 02:07:58,093
Rehabilitated?

1633
02:07:58,468 --> 02:08:00,303
It's just a bullshit word.

1634
02:08:01,263 --> 02:08:06,017
So you go on and stamp your forms,
sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1635
02:08:07,269 --> 02:08:09,520
Because to tell you the truth...

1636
02:08:09,855 --> 02:08:11,857
...I don't give a shit.

1637
02:09:38,401 --> 02:09:39,777
Here you go, miss.

1638
02:09:42,738 --> 02:09:43,739
Restroom break?

1639
02:09:49,578 --> 02:09:54,083
You don't need to ask me every time
you need to go take a piss. Just go.

1640
02:10:07,138 --> 02:10:10,224
Forty years I've been asking
permission to piss.

1641
02:10:11,058 --> 02:10:14,019
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

1642
02:10:17,565 --> 02:10:19,734
There's a harsh truth to face.

1643
02:10:21,402 --> 02:10:24,280
No way I'm going to make it
on the outside.

1644
02:10:32,163 --> 02:10:35,875
All I do anymore is think of ways
to break my parole...

1645
02:10:36,667 --> 02:10:39,128
...so maybe they'd send me back.

1646
02:10:44,341 --> 02:10:46,802
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

1647
02:10:47,678 --> 02:10:49,345
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

1648
02:10:49,555 --> 02:10:51,474
Knew it all too well.

1649
02:10:53,099 --> 02:10:56,479
All I want is to be back
where things make sense.

1650
02:10:56,937 --> 02:10:59,648
Where I won't have to be afraid
all the time.

1651
02:11:01,650 --> 02:11:04,028
Only one thing stops me.

1652
02:11:05,488 --> 02:11:07,865
A promise I made to Andy.

1653
02:11:28,386 --> 02:11:29,511
There it is.

1654
02:11:40,147 --> 02:11:41,816
Much obliged, sir.

1655
02:15:21,116 --> 02:15:22,369
Dear Red:

1656
02:15:22,619 --> 02:15:25,080
If you're reading this,
you've gotten out...

1657
02:15:25,287 --> 02:15:29,375
...and if you've come this far,
maybe you'd come a bit further.

1658
02:15:29,625 --> 02:15:32,086
You remember the name
of the town, don't you?

1659
02:15:34,421 --> 02:15:35,881
Zihuatanejo.

1660
02:15:37,549 --> 02:15:41,137
I could use a good man
to help me get my project on wheels.

1661
02:15:41,637 --> 02:15:45,183
I'll keep an eye out for you,
and the chessboard ready.

1662
02:15:45,974 --> 02:15:47,393
Remember, Red...

1663
02:15:47,726 --> 02:15:49,812
...hope is a good thing...

1664
02:15:50,020 --> 02:15:52,022
...maybe the best of things.

1665
02:15:52,232 --> 02:15:54,401
And no good thing ever dies.

1666
02:15:54,942 --> 02:15:57,778
I will be hoping
that this letter finds you...

1667
02:15:57,986 --> 02:15:59,738
...and finds you well.

1668
02:16:00,239 --> 02:16:01,448
Your friend...

1669
02:16:01,657 --> 02:16:02,825
...Andy.

1670
02:16:36,650 --> 02:16:38,402
"Get busy living...

1671
02:16:38,610 --> 02:16:40,486
...or get busy dying."

1672
02:16:43,198 --> 02:16:45,367
That's goddamn right.

1673
02:16:50,622 --> 02:16:52,750
For the second time in my life...

1674
02:16:53,000 --> 02:16:55,544
...I'm guilty of committing a crime.

1675
02:16:56,628 --> 02:16:58,546
Parole violation.

1676
02:16:59,214 --> 02:17:02,884
Of course I doubt they'll toss up
any roadblocks for that.

1677
02:17:03,552 --> 02:17:05,596
Not for an old crook like me.

1678
02:17:05,804 --> 02:17:07,806
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1679
02:17:11,518 --> 02:17:16,231
I find I'm so excited I can barely
sit still or hold a thought in my head.

1680
02:17:16,690 --> 02:17:19,985
I think it's the excitement
only a free man can feel.

1681
02:17:20,193 --> 02:17:22,696
A free man at the start
of a long journey...

1682
02:17:22,905 --> 02:17:25,491
...whose conclusion is uncertain.

1683
02:17:28,535 --> 02:17:31,162
I hope I can make it across the border.

1684
02:17:32,706 --> 02:17:35,709
I hope to see my friend
and shake his hand.

1685
02:17:37,586 --> 02:17:41,673
I hope the Pacific is as blue
as it has been in my dreams.

1686
02:17:43,509 --> 02:17:44,676
I hope.

